<br>
To the best of my knowledge, based on <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm28.showMessage?topicID=23.topic">Graffë's Wizard Library: Spell Casting Mastery</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   50% Specialization Conjuration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> reduces the cost by 2.5%, so rods cost 390 and yield 270 net mana.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   200% Specialization Conjuration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> reduces the cost by 10%, so rods cost 360 and yield 300 net mana.<br>
<br>
With <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Spell Casting Mastery</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> these numbers become:<br>
<br>
SCM1 + 50% Spec: 5% savings, 380 cost, 280 net mana.<br>
SCM2 + 50% Spec: 10% savings, 360 cost, 300 net mana.<br>
SCM3 + 50% Spec: 17.5% savings, 330 cost, 330 net mana.<br>
<br>
SCM1 + 200% Spec: 12.5% savings, 350 cost, 310 net mana.<br>
SCM2 + 200% Spec: 17.5% savings, 330 cost, 330 net mana.<br>
SCM3 + 200% Spec: 25% savings, 300 cost, 360 net mana.<br>
<br>
Focus items with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Mana Preservation III</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, such as the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Obolus Death Shroud</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, add another 40 mana cost savings and thus net mana.  The summoned focus earring does not save mana on summons.<br>
